Cultural agenda

Cultural agenda

   Culture is one of the building blocks of the Lyon Saint-Étienne
   university site, with cultural programs in its theaters and performance
   venues, gallery exhibitions and practical art, choir and orchestra
   workshops, etc.

   Our campuses are crammed full of cultural opportunities for students,
   staff and the general public. A number of schools on our site also
   train future professionals in cultural fields such as theater, dance,
   music and design, etc.

   In keeping with the 2013 Inter-Ministerial Higher Education and Culture
   Convention, "University, A Place of Culture", the Université de Lyon is
   committed to enhancing all its programs, training opportunities and
   research, and promotes wide-reaching on-site cultural initiatives with
   strong national outreach, such as the Arts and Culture in Higher
   Education Days (JACES), and international initiatives, like the Dance
   Biennale Parade.

Art(s) in Research seminar

Creative research in higher education

Peace Parade

2018 Dance Biennial

Arts and Culture in Higher Education Days

